        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 2:54PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 254 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Poverty Creek, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Poverty Creek and Portions of the Aldo Leopold Wilderness.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
